title: Jan Uytenbogaert, Remonstrant Preacher
provenance_text:
Rembrandt Harmensz van Rijn [1606-1669]. Kupferstichkabinett der Staatlichen Museen [1831-], Berlin, Germany, (L.1606) (L.2398) [1]; A. G. Thiermann [-1860?], (L.2434) [2]; Rudolf Philip Goldschmidt [1840-1914], Berlin, Germany, (L.2926); (Ehrich Galleries [1900?-1936], New York, NY, by 1924); purchased by Museum, November 1924. 
NOTES:1. Museum of Prints and Drawings. 2. The year of death is recorded in the Lugt database as either 1860 or 1861.
